      {
        "id": 3234056,
        "name": "Rohit 13h@\u00f1",
        "username": "Rohit_B",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/rohit_b/{size}/350939_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-09-11T15:49:37.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=149631&amp;iNote=9365676\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>1976 Ch\u00e2teau La Grave a Pomerol Trigant de Boisset</strong></a> <em>- France, Bordeaux, Libournais, Pomerol (9/10/2021)</em><br>\nNo rating because I\u2019ve never had anything like this. 45 years old!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Nose is entirely tertiary\u2014tobacco smoke, graphite, leather, tar, maybe some molasses, and some stringency from anise.</p>\n<p>Palate surprisingly has some red fruit left and reasonable acid. Extremely smooth and fills the mouth, but feels weightless. Medium bodied and fully resolved tannins.</p>\n<p>Finish is cherry stem, potting soil, wet forest floor, and quite long.</p>\n<p>I enjoyed it for the intellectual experiment that it was, but this is not a go-to wine at all. Not a crowd pleaser and not something I would serve without serious consideration of the consumer.</p>\n<p>45 years old!</p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em><br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/d/e/dec3e2be7c8207517a9d5e09a559fb4ec70efeee.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/dec3e2be7c8207517a9d5e09a559fb4ec70efeee\" title=\"IMG-5573.jpg\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/e/dec3e2be7c8207517a9d5e09a559fb4ec70efeee_2_666x500.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG-5573.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"vMFGgi14mjecpdKK8QZDs0LmAUe\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/e/dec3e2be7c8207517a9d5e09a559fb4ec70efeee_2_666x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/e/dec3e2be7c8207517a9d5e09a559fb4ec70efeee_2_999x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/d/e/dec3e2be7c8207517a9d5e09a559fb4ec70efeee_2_1332x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"46392C\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">IMG-5573.jpg</span><span class=\"informations\">4032\u00d73024 1.75 MB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div><br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/7/c/7c15f2643dcfde260126309936961d7c891914fe.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/7c15f2643dcfde260126309936961d7c891914fe\" title=\"IMG-5572.jpg\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/7/c/7c15f2643dcfde260126309936961d7c891914fe_2_666x500.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG-5572.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"hHIe5sMsFWbYtcz2Ai7joTGL9JI\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/7/c/7c15f2643dcfde260126309936961d7c891914fe_2_666x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/7/c/7c15f2643dcfde260126309936961d7c891914fe_2_999x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/7/c/7c15f2643dcfde260126309936961d7c891914fe_2_1332x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"594839\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">IMG-5572.jpg</span><span class=\"informations\">4032\u00d73024 2.23 MB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>",
